    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The enriched-category perspective comes from Lawvere's 1973 paper "Metric spaces, generalized logic, and closed categories." Milewski covers enriched categories in chapter 22 of Category Theory for Programmers, where the running example is exactly this: Bool-enrichment gives preorders, [0,&infin;]-enrichment gives metric spaces. The Hausdorff distance example uses finite sets for computability; the general definition uses suprema over arbitrary sets.</p>


